1️. Flexbox Layout
What is Flexbox?
Flexbox (Flexible Box Layout) is a CSS layout model used to:
a. Align items easily
b. Distribute space between elements
c. Build responsive layouts
d. Control row and column structures

<div class="container">
  <!-- inner blocks -->
</div>

.container {
  display: flex;
}

2️. Flex Direction – Row

By default, flex items are placed in a row (left to right).
Example:
<div class="container">
  <div class="box">Box 1</div>
  <div class="box">Box 2</div>
  <div class="box">Box 3</div>
</div>

.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;   /* default */
  gap: 10px;
}

.box {
  background-color: lightblue;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 1px solid blue;
}

3️. Flex Direction – Column

When we change direction to column, items stack vertically.
Usage:

.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 10px;
}

Output:

Box1
Box2
Box3

