5. Media Queries (Responsiveness)

What is Responsiveness?
Responsiveness means:-
a. Website adjusts layout based on screen size
b. Works on mobile, tablet, desktop  


@media (max-width: 768px) {
  /* CSS for smaller screens */
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  /* CSS for smaller screens */
}

max-width → applies below this screen size
min-width → applies above this screen size 

Example:

    <div class="main">
        <div>
            conatiner 1
        </div>
         <div>
            conatiner 2
        </div>
         <div>
            conatiner 3
        </div>
         <div>
            conatiner 4
        </div>
         <div>
            conatiner 5
        </div>
    </div>


.main {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  border: black 1px solid;
}


/* mobile devices/screens */
@media (max-width: 576px) {
  .main {
    background-color: aquamarine;
  }
}

/* tabs/ipads */
@media (min-width: 577px) and (max-width: 768px) {
  .main {
    display: block;
    background-color: blue;
  }
}

/* desktops/laptops/PCs */
@media (min-width:769px)  {
  .main{
    background-color: brown;
    display: block;
  }
}

