HTML provides elements to embed multimedia content like videos and audio directly in webpages.

Common multimedia elements:

<video> → For videos
<audio> → For audio files
<iframe> → To embed external content

1.Video Element
The <video> element is used to embed/insert videos from our local project in a webpage without external plugins.

Supported formats include:
a. MP4
b .WebM

Example-1:
<video width="400" controls autoplay muted loop>
  <source src="sample-video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  Your browser does not support the video tag.
</video>

Example-2:
<video src="demo.mp4" width="400" height="350" controls >
  </video>

Note: Both Examples will work.


| Attribute  | Purpose                   |
| ---------- | ------------------------- |
| `width`    | Sets video width          |
| `controls` | Shows play, pause, volume |
| `<source>` | Defines video file        |

Real-Time Usage

Used in:
Product demos
Tutorials
Landing pages
Online courses (Training Institute Platforms)

2.Audio Element
The <audio> element is used to play sound files on webpages.

Supported formats:
MP3
Ogg

Example-1:
<audio controls>
  <source src="song.mp3" type="audio/mp3">
  Your browser does not support the audio element.
</audio>

<audio src="sample-3s.mp3" controls loop autoplay></audio>


| Attribute  | Purpose                  |
| ---------- | ------------------------ |
| `controls` | Shows play/pause buttons |
| `autoplay` | Plays automatically      |
| `loop`     | Repeats audio            |


Real-Time Usage:

Music websites
Podcasts
Meditation apps
Language learning platforms

